            "name": "Inhabit Vessel",
            "subtype": "ability",
            "text": "The lion touches and melds with its bonded vessel, bringing the statue to life. It can cease Inhabiting its Vessel by Dismissing the effect. While Inhabiting the Vessel, it loses its fly Speed and gains: Immunities healing, nonlethal; but Resistances physical 5 (except bludgeoning), Speed 20 feet, and it gains the following Strikes. \n* **Melee**  [#] jaws +14, **Damage** 2d6+7 bludgeoning plus Grab\n* **Ranged**  [#] stone ball +13 (range increment 30 feet), **Damage** 2d4+7 bludgeoning",
